HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 58
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Ernest Hamilton "Buddy"
Parks of Chattanooga.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Ernest Hamilton "Buddy" Parks of Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, Ernest Hamilton Parks was an exemplary gentleman and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in 1932 to a Chattanoogan family of storied and successful
contractors, Mr. Parks graduated from Central High School and then the University of
Chattanooga, where he earned a bachelor's degree in engineering physics and a commission
as a second lieutenant in the United States Army; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Parks, having married his beloved wife, Mackie Sue Roberts, and
desiring to serve his country, moved to Oklahoma to act as an instructor at Fort Sill; and
WHEREAS, he went on to work at Combustion Engineering, and after his retirement in
the 1980s, he began to manage some of the properties of former U.S. Senator Bob Corker,
including such distinguished Chattanoogan structures as the James Building and the Volunteer
Building; and
WHEREAS, the rejuvenating influence of Mr. Parks's management also extended to the
famous Dome Building and nearby Customs House, both of which have merited recognition on
the National Register of Historic Places; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Parks did not content himself with overseeing the affairs of this world
but also busied himself with caring for the souls at Hixson Church of Christ; and
